11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 650.12 of Title 21, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 A. Every person who, without justifiable or excusable cause and
16 with intent to do bodily harm, commits any assault upon the person
17 of a municipal, county, or state official who is in the lawful
18 performance of his or her duties of employment, upon conviction, is
19 guilty of a misdemeanor and shall be punished by imprisonment in the
20 county jail for a term not to exceed one (1) year, or by a fine not
21 to exceed One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00), or by both such fine and
22 imprisonment.
23 B. Every person who, without justifiable or excusable cause and
24 with intent to do bodily harm, commits any battery or assault and
