1 batt ery upon the person of a municipal, county, or state official
2 who is in the lawful performance of his or her duties of employment,
3 upon conviction, is guilty of a felony and shall be punished by
4 imprisonment in the custody of the Department of Corrections for a
5 term not to exceed five (5) years, or by a fine not to exceed Five
6 Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00), or by both such fine and imprisonment.
7 C. As used in this section, "official" means any code
8 enforcement official, zoning official, fire official, police
9 official, health official, safety official, building official, or
10 deputies thereof, or any other person designated by county
11 legislation, municipal ordinance, or state statutes to lawfully
12 investigate, enforce, or perform duties set within such legislation,
13 ordinance, or statutes, as adopted by the governing body thereof.
14 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
